#!/bin/bash

cat << 'EOF'
ðŸ§˜ Zen - Complete Terminal Environment

NAVIGATION & FILES
------------------
ls, lsa     - List files with icons (lsa = show hidden)
ll          - Detailed list view
lt, lta     - Tree view (lta = show hidden)
cd          - Smart cd with zoxide (remembers frequent dirs)
..          - Go up one directory
mkcd <dir>  - Create directory and cd into it
ff          - Fuzzy file finder with preview
findf       - Find files by name
findd       - Find directories by name

GIT SHORTCUTS
-------------
g           - git
gs          - git status
ga          - git add
gc          - git commit
gcm         - git commit -m "message"
gcom        - Conventional commit (e.g., gcom feat "add feature")
gp          - git push
gpl         - git pull
gl          - git log (pretty)
gcl <url>   - Clone repo and cd into it
gnb <name>  - Create new branch and switch
gchanged    - Show files changed in last commit
gundo       - Undo last commit (keep changes)
lzg         - LazyGit (interactive git UI)

DOCKER
------
d           - docker
dc          - docker-compose
dps         - docker ps
di          - docker images
dex         - docker exec -it
denter      - Enter running container
lzd         - LazyDocker (interactive docker UI)
docker-cleanup     - Clean up all docker resources
docker-rm-stopped  - Remove all stopped containers
docker-rm-images   - Remove dangling images

PYTHON
------
py          - python3
uv          - UV package manager
venv        - Create and activate venv with UV
uv-init     - Create venv and activate
uv-activate - Activate existing venv

EDITOR
------
v, vim, n   - Open neovim
nvim .      - Open neovim in current directory

TMUX
----
t           - tmux
ta          - tmux attach
tn <name>   - Create NEW named session (always creates)
tm [name]   - Smart attach: tries to attach first, creates if doesn't exist

SYSTEM
------
top         - btop (beautiful process monitor)
disk        - Show disk usage
duh         - Disk usage sorted (current directory)
meminfo     - Show memory info
myip        - Show public IP (auto-copies to clipboard)
localip     - Show local IP (auto-copies to clipboard)
ports       - Show open ports
killp       - Kill process by name

UTILITIES
---------
extract     - Extract any archive type
compress    - Create tar.gz archive
backup      - Backup a file with timestamp
serve       - Start HTTP server (default: port 8000)
search      - Search text in files (uses ripgrep)
hgrep       - Search command history
count       - Count files in directory
weather     - Check weather
cheat <cmd> - Show cheatsheet for command
genpass     - Generate random password
note [text] - Quick notes (saves to ~/.notes/YYYY-MM-DD.md)
              Usage: note "your note text" OR note (opens editor)

ZEN COMMANDS
------------
zupdate [tags]  - Update Zen from repo (skips if up to date)
                  Examples: zupdate, zupdate shell, zupdate "shell,cli-tools"
zsetdir [path]  - Set/show Zen directory location
                  Examples: zsetdir ~/projects/zen, zsetdir (show current)
zcleanup        - Clean up backup files created by Zen
                  Examples: zcleanup, zcleanup --force
zhelp           - Show this help message

SHELL MANAGEMENT
----------------
aliases         - Edit aliases in editor
functions       - Edit functions in editor
reload          - Reload shell configuration

Happy coding! ðŸŽ‰
